1. pip install --upgrade pip

2. pip install pdf2image

3. pip install opencv-python

4. pip install pytesseract

5. pip install pdfkit

6. Conda: conda install -c conda-forge poppler
   Mac: brew install poppler
   Archlinux: sudo pacman -S poppler
   Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install poppler-utils

7. Download wkhtmltopdf here: https://wkhtmltopdf.org/downloads.html

8. Drag entire folder, usually in C:/Users/[USER], into pycharm project, usually in C:/Users/[USER]/PycharmProjects/[PROJECT NAME]

9. Change filepath in @turnToImage.py to the location in drive. Keep "wkhtmltopdf/bin/wkhtmltopdf.exe"

10. Run main.py after adding link to NY Times article

11. Set project encoding to windows-1252 (open bodyText file in TextFiles after running main, and click message at top)